	<h1>Housekeeping</h1>Well, blogger seems to be overwhelmed right now and my last edit failed.  I will do more later, but I want this posted just for safe-keeping, disorganized as it is.<h2><font color="009900">Very loose ends -- long list</font></h2><<a href="http://www.newsfactor.com/perl/printer/20785/">Digital Vaccine May Make Computer Networks Tolerant to a Fault</a>.&nbsp; Mike Martin, NewsFactor Network, February 18, 2003.&nbsp; I am particularly interested in how this works with respect to CORBA and distributed objects, something that is a concern for me on <a href="http://miser-theory.info/">The Miser Project</a>.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#89395494">Wednesday, February 19, 2003</a></span></div>
